---
date: 2026-06-19
topic: trailblazers
level: medium
---

Eadweard Muybridge lined a dozen cameras along Leland Stanford's Palo Alto track today in 1878 and wired each shutter to a thread the mare, Sallie Gardner, snapped as she galloped past — twelve exposures, a thousandth of a second each. They answered a question painters had only guessed at: a running horse does lift all four hooves at once, but gathered beneath its body, never in the splayed mid-air stretch the old canvases drew. Run the stills back in order and the horse moves again. Motion pictures start here — on a question about a horse.
